<taxonomicName authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1877" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Harttia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="241" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="loricariformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="241">Harttia loricariformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents 2 large and trapezoid preanal plates touching the small anterior plates (
<bibRefCitation author="Langeani F &amp; Oyakawa OT &amp; Montoya-Burgos JI" box="[539,760,1519,1544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="241" pagination="136 - 142" refId="ref7230" refString="Langeani F, Oyakawa OT, Montoya-Burgos JI (2001) New species of Harttia (Loricariidae, Loricariinae) from the rio Sao Francisco basin. Copeia 2001, 136 - 142. http: // doi. org / 10.1643 / 0045 - 8511 (2001) 001 [0136: NSOHLL] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">Langeani et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
